==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remittance
<hw>Re*mit"tance</hw> <pr>(r?-m?t"t<it>a</it>ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of transmitting money, bills, or the like, esp.
to a distant place, as in satisfaction of a demand, or in discharge of
an obligation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The sum or thing remitted.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remittee</ent>⟦br⟧
